SIMPLE: null
RECORDS: 4

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Null
<hw>Null</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>nullus</ets> not
any, none; <ets>ne</ets> not + <ets>ullus</ets> any, a dim. of
<ets>unus</ets> one; cf. F. <ets>nul</ets>. See <er>No</er>, and
<er>One</er>, and cf. <er>None</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Of no legal
or binding force or validity; of no efficacy; invalid; void; nugatory;
useless.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Faultily faultless, icily regular, splendidly <qex>null</qex>,⟦br⟧
Dead perfection; no more.</q> <rj><qau>Tennyson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Having a value of zero; <as>as, of <ex>null</ex>
utility</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Math.)</fld> <def>Empty; having no members; <as>as,
the <ex>null</ex> set</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <fld>(Computers)</fld> <def>Unassigned or meaningless; --
a special value given to variables, especially pointers or logical
variables, indicating that it is meaningless and cannot be used in
computation; <as>as, an uninitialized pointer in "C" is given a
<ex>null</ex> value</as>. The actual value that is stored in memory to
indicate the <ex>null</ex> condition may vary with the computer language
used.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Null</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Null
<hw>Null</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Something that has no
force or meaning.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That which has no value; a cipher; zero.</def>
<rj><au>Bacon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Null method</b></col> <fld>(Physics.)</fld>, <cd>a zero
method. See under <er>Zero</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Null</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Null
<hw>Null</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[From <ets>null</ets>, a., or perh.
abbrev. from <ets>annul</ets>.]</ety> <def>To annul.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Null</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 4 ====
HEADWORD: Null
<hw>Null</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Etymol. uncertain.]</ety> <def>One of
the beads in <cref>nulled work</cref>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Nullah</ent>⟦br⟧
